    <stitle>FRONT STEER AXLE: EATON E1200I I-BEAM - OVERHAUL PROCEDURES - STEERING KNUCKLE DISASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>STEERING KNUCKLE DISASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the slack adjuster to return brake shoes to the released position and clear drum.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove hub cap, cotter pin, nut, washer, and outer bearing cone assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove wheel and hub assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect air or hydraulic line from the brake assembly.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Plug or cap line and cylinder to prevent hydraulic fluid contamination.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove brake assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove cotter pin and slotted nut from the tie rod end (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200707">Figure 7</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200707" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200707" filename="../figg02/G0200707.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Cotter Pin/Slotted Nut Removal</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect tie rod end from tie rod arm using a suitable tool such as a pickle fork (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200708">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200708" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200708" filename="../figg02/G0200708.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Disconnect Tie Rod End</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Do not use heat on any axle parts or fasteners.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect drag link from steering arm by removing cotter pin and slotted nut.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove top and bottom knuckle caps and gaskets.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove nut from draw key, then drive key out using a hammer and brass drift (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200709">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200709" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200709" filename="../figg02/G0200709.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Drive Key Out</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drive kingpin out with a hammer and brass drift (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200710">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200710" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200710" filename="../figg02/G0200710.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Drive Kingpin Out</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove steering knuckle from axle beam.</para>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Wear safe eye protection. Do not hit steel parts with a steel hammer. Parts can break and
                        cause injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
